menu "Slave OTA (C6 coprocessor)"

    config OTA_SLAVE_FORCE_FLASH
        bool "Force unconditional C6 re-flash on next boot"
        default n
        help
            When enabled, the P4 re-flashes the embedded C6 firmware from the
            slave_fw partition on every boot until CONFIG_OTA_SLAVE_FORCE_FLASH
            is cleared and the P4 is reflashed. Skips the C6 application
            version query and the embedded-vs-C6 version comparison. Use this
            to recover a C6 that is stuck in a boot loop / not responding to
            RPC (e.g. after a bad ESP-NOW firmware flash).

            Normal boot flow:
                1. Query C6 app version via custom RPC.
                2. Only OTA if the version differs from the embedded binary.

            Force flow (this option):
                1. Wait for SDIO transport only (no RPC version query).
                2. Always run esp_hosted_slave_ota_{begin,write,end,activate}.
                3. Clear the force flag after activation so the next boot
                   returns to the normal verify path (unless you rebuild with
                   this option still set).

            IMPORTANT: remember to re-embed the updated C6 binary into the
            slave_fw partition (rebuild + reflash the P4) before enabling
            this option, otherwise you will just re-write the same broken
            firmware that is already on the C6.

endmenu
